<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900719-0135</DOCNO><DOCID>900719-0135.</DOCID><HL>   Pier 1's June Sales Up</HL><DATE>07/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><CO>   PIR</CO><LP>   FORT WORTH, Texas -- Pier 1 Imports said that sales rosealmost 12% in June but that sales for those at stores openmore than a year fell 2.6%.   The company attributed the slip in sales at older storesto a decline in furniture sales. &quot;The consumer has lost alittle confidence in the economy and is buying lessfurniture,&quot; said Robert G. Herndon, chief financial officerfor the home-furnishing retailer. Mr. Herndon said thecompany's sales of soft goods remain strong.</LP><TEXT>   In June, Pier 1 had sales of $56.9 million, up from $50.9million a year ago.</TEXT></DOC>